for as long as you live on your death bed you will never never forget this person describe this person in i was at a club at the alexandria hotel in downtown los angeles nursing a beer and crying when a marachi playing music saw me he told me no llores thats spanish for dont cry riddle me this for as long as you live even on your death bed describe to me and to readers a person who you will never never forget and why actually the person i remember was a year old kid who looked like he was because of scarring he had incurred in a boiler accident he was with a group of three other friends at a resort hotel in panama city beach florida i must admit it took a little getting used to looking at him but i was amazed by his spirit despite the hardships he had suffered he laughed and enjoyed himself and wasn't afraid to live as if he were normal in appearance i was and still continue to be in admiration of his courage the injuries changed him in a way that most of us could never imagine yet he celebrated his life and didn't seem to be filled with any self pity Zhao Yun W.I.T.C.H. She Loves You Jon Secada Charly Garc__a Atlas Comics (1950s) Walt Disney Rich Mullins The Catcher in the Rye Shawn Michaels Humphrey Bogart Night (book) Highway 61 Revisited Fruits Basket Piccolo Junior Saga Friends Milton H. Erickson Jack Kerouac Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Make money fast John Berryman Marilyn Monroe EastEnders Florida East Coast Railway Marie Antoinette The Contender (television series) Reincarnation Pitaten Stroke Los Angeles, California Sheraton Hotel The Emancipation of Mimi Ben Johnson (athlete) Obi-Wan Kenobi The Doors Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Lord Voldemort Buster Keaton Memento (film) Los Angeles Kings Jessica Lynch Walt Disney World Resort Sharon Stone Blonde on Blonde Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Sami Brady Darth Vader The Lovely Bones Up at the Villa Hypnosis Walt Disney Parks and Resorts The Freewheelin' B